# {{title .Name}}

A charmbracelet v2 TUI application scaffolded with [spin](https://github.com/example/spin).

## Prerequisites

- Go 1.25.0+ (charmbracelet v2 libraries require Go 1.25.0)
- [Task](https://taskfile.dev) for the dev workflow (optional; the Make-less alternative)

## Quick start

```sh
task setup      # install gofumpt, goimports, air, prism
task run        # run with hot reload
```

Or run directly:

```sh
go run .
```

## Next steps

- `go run .` — launch the TUI
- `task setup` — install gofumpt, goimports, air, prism
- `task run` — launch with hot reload
- `task test` — run tests via prism (or `go test ./...` if prism is not installed)
- `task fmt` — format with gofumpt + goimports
- `task vet` — run `go vet ./...`
- `task build` — produce `./bin/{{.Name}}`
- `task clean` — remove `./bin` and `./tmp`
{{ if hasGlow . -}}
- `glow README.md` — preview the README in the terminal (glow is a binary, not a Go import; install with `go install github.com/charmbracelet/glow/v2@latest`)
{{- end}}

## Project layout

- `main.go` — the bubbletea v2 program (model + Update + View)
- `go.mod` — module declaration with pinned charmbracelet v2 dependencies
- `internal/ui/styles.go` — lipgloss v2 styles (when --lipgloss is enabled)
- `.air.toml` — hot-reload configuration
- `Taskfile.yml` — dev workflow tasks
- `README.md` — this file
- `LICENSE` — license file (MIT by default)
- `.gitignore` — generated ignore patterns

